# Release Versioning

This Composer package uses git tags as the source of truth for package versions.

- Do not add a `version` field to `composer.json`.
- Prepare releases by committing the code changes, then creating a matching git tag such as `v0.2.4`.
- Packagist/Composer resolves the package version from the git tag.
- If `composer.json` changes, run `composer update --lock` and review the lockfile before release.
